                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/27: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-06T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 6, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. The fleet has returned to Coquimbo after capturing a Chilean commercial
                    vessel carrying some supplies. All coastwise traffic has <pb facs="1028" n="914"
                        xml:id="pg_914"/> been suspended and Valparaiso is filled with troops. Our
                    consular office reports no damage to American commercial interests as a result
                    of the fighting in Talcahuano. The Government has called for volunteers and
                    certain reserve officers have been ordered to report for duty.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Lima.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
